{
  "texts": [
    "Briefly, Samtools 87 (v.1.16) mpileup command was used to generate a mpileup file from matched germline and tumor BAM files with duplicates removed.",
    "If a matched germline was not available, a high-quality normal sample was used to pair with the tumor sample.",
    "VarScan 88 (v.2.3.5) was then used to take the mpileup file to call somatic CNVs after adjusting for normal/tumor sample read coverage depth and GC content.",
    "Circular Binary Segmentation algorithm 89 implemented in the DNAcopy R package (v.1.52.0) was used to identify the candidate CNVs for each sample.",
    "B-allele frequency information was also used to assess allelic imbalance."
  ]
}